page.title: 19OLD SULEHAY FOREST
page.content: Old Sulehay Forest is the north part ofthe ancient Rockingham Forest. It is a very dense forest with a lot of trees. The main trees are Oak, Hazel, and Hawthorn. The wood is about I square kilometre. The most common tree in the forest is hazel. In 100 square metres 61 trees are hazel out of 115 ; that is more than half. A PH reading of 6.5 average indicates Hazel trees prefer slightly acidic soil as well as moist soil. The forest floor is muddy with ground being very moist. The moisture helps the trees to grow. The wood has a big path going through it for people. The wood has lots of different plants and animals. Not a lot of light gets through the leaves of the trees so the forest is dark and gloomy.
